  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "47-54. What do we? for this man doeth many miracles—\"While we trifle, 'this man,' by His 'many miracles,' will carry all before Him; the popular enthusiasm will bring on a revolution, which will precipitate the Romans upon us, and our all will go down in one common ruin.\" What a testimony to the reality of our Lord's miracles, and their resistless effect, from His bitterest enemies!",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
